name: OSD (On-Site Stormwater Detention) Tank #22
Site Preparation
1.1 Inspect the excavation and preparation of the site for detention tank installation, ensuring proper compaction and leveling.
Detention Tank Installation
2.1 Tank Structure: Verify the construction materials (e.g., reinforced concrete, plastic, steel) and dimensions of the detention tank.
Details: As per Australian Standard AS/NZS 3500
2.2 Inlet and Outlet Structures: Inspect the installation and alignment of inlet and outlet pipes, including flow control devices (e.g., weirs, valves).
Details: As per Australian Standard AS/NZS 3500
2.3 Sediment Traps: Ensure sediment traps or other filtration systems are installed to prevent debris from entering the detention tank
Details: As per Australian Standard AS/NZS 3500
Connection to Drainage System
3.1 Piping and Connections: Inspect the connection of detention tank pipes to the existing drainage system or discharge point.
Details: As per Australian Standard AS/NZS 3500
3.2 Backflow Prevention: Verify the installation of backflow prevention devices where necessary to protect against flooding and contamination.
Details: As per Australian Standard AS/NZS 3500
Testing and Commissioning
4.1 Hydraulic Testing: Conduct hydraulic testing to verify the capacity and functionality of the detention tank under design flow conditions.
Details: As per Australian Standard AS/NZS 3500
4.2 Control Device Testing: Test and calibrate flow control devices to ensure they regulate discharge rates as per design specifications.
Details: As per Australian Standard AS/NZS 3500
4.3 Safety Checks: Ensure all safety features, such as access covers and warning signs, are installed and functional.
Details: As per Australian Standard AS/NZS 3500
Operational Readiness
5.1 Documentation Review: Verify all installation records, test reports, and as-built drawings are complete and accurate.
Details: As per Australian Standard AS/NZS 3500
5.2 Training: Ensure personnel responsible for detention tank operation are trained in its use, maintenance, and emergency procedures
Details: As per Australian Standard AS/NZS 3500
Final Inspection
6.1 Visual Inspection: Conduct a final visual inspection of the detention tank installation and surroundings for compliance with safety and environmental standards.
Details: As per Australian Standard AS/NZS 3500
6.2 Functional Testing: Perform a functional test of the detention tank system to ensure it operates as intended under varying flow conditions.
Details: As per Australian Standard AS/NZS 3500
Screw Piles #23
Site Preparation
1.1 Survey and Marking: Verify accurate survey and marking of pile locations
Details: As per Australian Standard AS 2159
1.2 Inspect the site for readiness and clearance of obstructions
Details: As per Australian Standard AS 2159
1.3 Equipment Check: Check calibration certificates and maintenance records of equipment
Details: As per Australian Standard AS 2159
1.4 Conduct a visual inspection to ensure equipment is in working condition
Details: As per Australian Standard AS 2159
Screw Pile Installation
2.1 Ensure verticality and correct depth of installed piles
Details: As per Australian Standard AS 2159
2.2 Record and review torque values.
Details: As per Australian Standard AS 2159
2.3 Confirm alignment and positioning with design specifications.
Details: As per Australian Standard AS 2159
Post-Installation Inspection
3.1 Verify the height of cut piles and proper installation of caps
Details: As per Australian Standard AS 2159
3.2 Perform load tests according to specified procedures
Details: As per Australian Standard AS 2159
3.3 Analyze and document load test results.
Details: As per Australian Standard AS 2159
Final Inspection
4.1 Perform a thorough visual check of installed piles
Details: As per Australian Standard AS 2159
4.2 Ensure site cleanliness and safety
Details: As per Australian Standard AS 2159
Cupolex #28
Material Inspection & Site Preparation
1.1 Review material certificates and delivery documentation.
Details: As per Australian Standard AS 3600, AS 2870, AS/NZS 4671
1.2 Conduct a visual inspection for physical damage or defects
Details: As per Australian Standard AS 3600, AS 2870, AS/NZS 4671
1.3 Inspect ground preparation for levelness and compaction.
Details: As per Australian Standard AS 3600, AS 2870, AS/NZS 4671
1.4 Measure and verify the installation area dimensions.
Details: As per Australian Standard AS 3600, AS 2870, AS/NZS 4671
Installation
2.1 Cupolex Formwork Positioning: Ensure proper leveling and stability of the formwork.
Details: As per Australian Standard AS 3600, AS 2870, AS/NZS 4671
2.2 Reinforcement Installation: Inspect the placement, alignment, and securement of reinforcement.
Details: As per Australian Standard AS 3600, AS 2870, AS/NZS 4671
2.3 Concrete Pouring: Check concrete mix, placement, and compaction techniques. Ensure no voids or honeycombing in the concrete.
Details: As per Australian Standard AS 3600, AS 2870, AS/NZS 4671
Post-Installation Inspection
3.1 Concrete Curing: Monitor curing process and ensure compliance with curing specifications.
Details: As per Australian Standard AS 3600, AS 2870, AS/NZS 4671
3.2 Formwork Removal: Check for any damage or defects during formwork removal.
Details: As per Australian Standard AS 3600, AS 2870, AS/NZS 4671
Final Inspection
4.1 Perform a thorough visual check of the installed structure
Details: As per Australian Standard AS 3600, AS 2870, AS/NZS 4671
4.2 Test for structural integrity and verify the functionality of the system
Details: As per Australian Standard AS 3600, AS 2870, AS/NZS 4671
Retaining Wall #29
Pre-Construction Inspection
1.1 Site Assessment: Conduct a geotechnical survey and review soil reports
Details: As per Australian Standard AS 4678, AS/NZS 1170, AS 3600, AS 3700
1.2 Material Inspection: Verify that all materials (e.g., concrete, masonry blocks, reinforcement) meet the required specifications and are free from damage or defects upon delivery
Details: As per Australian Standard AS 4678, AS/NZS 1170, AS 3600, AS 3700
Site Preparation
2.1 Excavation and Foundation Preparation: Check the dimensions, depth, and compaction of the excavation.
Details: As per Australian Standard AS 4678, AS/NZS 1170, AS 3600, AS 3700
2.2 Ensure the foundation is level and free of loose material.
Details: As per Australian Standard AS 4678, AS/NZS 1170, AS 3600, AS 3700
Formwork and Reinforcement
3.1 Check the placement, alignment, and securement of formwork and reinforcement
Details: As per Australian Standard AS 4678, AS/NZS 1170, AS 3600, AS 3700
Concrete Pouring
4.1 Check concrete mix, placement, and compaction technique
Details: As per Australian Standard AS 4678, AS/NZS 1170, AS 3600, AS 3700
4.2 Ensure no voids or honeycombing in the concrete
Details: As per Australian Standard AS 4678, AS/NZS 1170, AS 3600, AS 3700
Masonry Wall Construction (if applicable)
5.1 Verify the construction of masonry retaining walls, including the laying of blocks and application of mortar.
Details: As per Australian Standard AS 4678, AS/NZS 1170, AS 3600, AS 3700
Drainage Installation
6.1 Check the placement and alignment of drainage pipes and outlets.
Details: As per Australian Standard AS 4678, AS/NZS 1170, AS 3600, AS 3700
Backfilling
7.1 Inspect the backfill material and compaction methods
Details: As per Australian Standard AS 4678, AS/NZS 1170, AS 3600, AS 3700
7.2 Ensure backfill is placed in layers and compacted to the required density.
Details: As per Australian Standard AS 4678, AS/NZS 1170, AS 3600, AS 3700
Post-Construction Inspection
8.1 Monitor curing process and ensure compliance with curing specifications.
Details: As per Australian Standard AS 4678, AS/NZS 1170, AS 3600, AS 3700
8.2 Perform visual and, if necessary, non-destructive testing (NDT) to check for cracks or structural weaknesses.
Details: As per Australian Standard AS 4678, AS/NZS 1170, AS 3600, AS 3700
Final Inspection
9.1 Perform a thorough visual check of the retaining wall.
Details: As per Australian Standard AS 4678, AS/NZS 1170, AS 3600, AS 3700
9.2 Test for structural integrity and verify the functionality of drainage systems.
Details: As per Australian Standard AS 4678, AS/NZS 1170, AS 3600, AS 3700
